<div id="review_213786936" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/213786936" />
    <a title="Jim" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4769683-jim"><img alt="Jim" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1294433436p2/4769683.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/213786936?book_show_action=true">Sep 23, 2011</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jim" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jim" href="/user/show/4769683-jim">Jim</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer213786936" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10424349580272030995">Great book uncovering the truly mysterious life of Moe Berg. Follows Berg through his beginnings to retirement from baseball, examining his potential role in the OSS. Was he working for the US government, or was he just a whacky ballplayer that participated in some strange things while playing ball. You decide.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


